      "widgets_values": [
        "SHARP -> Repose -> Nano Banana Camera-Locked Repair\n\n1. Load your photo  2. SHARP runs locally -> creates Gaussian splat  3. Repose the camera in GaussianViewer Lift and click 'Set Camera'  4. Queue prompt -> the workflow writes a repair prompt from the original + reposed images, then asks Nano Banana to edit only the reposed render so the view stays anchored."
      ],
      "_meta": {
        "title": "Workflow Guide"
      },
      "color": "#233",
      "bgcolor": "#355"
    },
